        <h2>Safety Planning Tips</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Have an emergency escape plan ready, including a packed bag with essentials.</li>
            <li>Keep important documents, emergency money, and phone numbers accessible.</li>
            <li>Identify a safe place to go and people you can trust.</li>
            <li>Use a secure phone or device to seek help and clear browsing history if needed.</li>
            <li>If you are a Kaiser Permanente member, contact the Employee Assistance Program (EAP) for free, confidential counseling.</li>
